				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$r=\frac{{\rm{\Delta }}C}{{t}_{r}}.$$\end{document}r=ΔCtr.

As a quantitative measure of the transition we propose the use of tipping probabilities. In noisy systems this concept has already turned out to be useful31. The novelty of our approach lies in applying tipping probabilities to fully deterministic systems. This quantity is based on the scenario-dependent basins of attraction mentioned above. The tipping probability \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
